<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-234] Customizable Cookie Policy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-234</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Even if the server is not complying with the cookie specification, sometimes &lt;br/&gt;
you still need to talk to it.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It would be nice that when setting the Cookie Policy for the HttpMethod, you &lt;br/&gt;
could specify a custom policy that implements the CookieSpecBase but may &lt;br/&gt;
handle certain problems more leniently.  This would be instead of specifying &lt;br/&gt;
one of the three hard-coded policies.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
