                    <comment id="12380682" author="olegk" created="Sat, 28 Jun 2003 02:18:27 +0100"  >We do plan to provide a plug-in mechanism for custom cookie policies in post-2.0&lt;br/&gt;
releases. This feature has been on our to-do list for quite some time&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12380683" author="olegk" created="Sun, 19 Oct 2003 21:29:34 +0100"  >Created an attachment (id=8618)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch (take 1)&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12380684" author="olegk" created="Sun, 19 Oct 2003 21:33:34 +0100"  >The patch extends CookiePolicy class with a custom cookie specification plug-in&lt;br/&gt;
mechanism. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Let me know what you think.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
                    <comment id="12380685" author="becke@u.washington.edu" created="Sun, 19 Oct 2003 23:43:13 +0100"  >Oleg,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This looks good.  Nice work.  I have only two minor comments:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- CookiePolicy.getSpecByVersion(int) should be deprecated I think.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- All of the static methods in CookiePolicy should be grouped together.  Preferably after the static &lt;br/&gt;
params I think.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mike</comment>
                    <comment id="12380686" author="olegk" created="Mon, 20 Oct 2003 00:51:53 +0100"  >&amp;gt;  - CookiePolicy.getSpecByVersion(int) should be deprecated I think.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I was not sure if I should deprecate this one, as it arguably could still be&lt;br/&gt;
useful. But because this method is not flexible enough (one cannot change cookie&lt;br/&gt;
specs associated with cookie versions) I agree it should be deprecated&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; - All of the static methods in CookiePolicy should be grouped together.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;ll do so.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
